# Requirements and Compliance Models

!!! note "How to read model answers"
    Model answers should be analysed, not memorised. Compare them against your own draft to identify improvements in structure, evidence handling, terminology, and documentary usefulness.

## Weak statement

> The unit should be robust and work well in difficult conditions.

## Stronger requirement statement

> The unit shall maintain nominal functional performance within the environmental conditions defined in the applicable qualification profile.

## Why the stronger version is better

The stronger version is better because it removes vague adjectives, introduces requirement modality, and links the claim to a defined reference boundary rather than to undefined â€œdifficult conditionsâ€.

## Verification-oriented requirement set

1. The enclosure shall provide mechanical protection to the connector interface during normal handling and scheduled maintenance access.
2. The connector retention feature shall prevent unintended disengagement under the handling conditions defined in the applicable maintenance procedure.
3. Compliance shall be demonstrated through inspection and functional verification in accordance with the approved verification plan.

## Teacher note

At premium level, ask whether every requirement could be matched to an objective verification method. If not, the wording is still incomplete.

